MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 612660463}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 962607de9302ee54887c1298ff58e483, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialgueManager
  currentLineIndex: 0
  dialogueText: {fileID: 2005818542}
  speakerNameText: {fileID: 94045592}
  dialogueLines:
  - Ten duel commandments
  - 'Number 1: The challenge demands satisfaction. If they apologise, no need for
    further action'
  - 'Number 2: Grab a friend, that''s your second, your lieutenant when there''s
    recockinging to be reckonded '
  - 'Number 3: Have your seconds meet face-to-face. Negotiate a peace or negotiate
    a time and place.'
  - 'Number 4: If you can''t make a peace, that''s alright. Time to get some pistols
    and a doctor on site. Pay her in advance, treat her with civility, and have turn
    turn around so she can have deniability.'
  - 'Number 5: Duel before teh sun is in the sky. Pick a place to die where it''s
    high and dry.'
  - 'Number 6: Leave a note for your next of of kin, tell them where you''ve been,
    pray that Hell or Heaven lets you in.'
  - 'Number 7: Confess your sins, ready for the moment of adreneline when you finally
    face your opponent.'
  - 'Number 8: Last chace to negotitaew. Send in your seconds, see if they can set
    the record straight.'
  - 'Number 9: Look him in the eye, aim no higher. Summon all the curage you require,
    then count 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9'
  - 'Number 10: Places. Fire!'
  dialogueUI: {fileID: 395729943}
  speakerNameUI: {fileID: 485269591}
